DFT calculations with periodic boundary conditions (PBC) were carried out using the program ADF-BAND 2019. Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof exchange-correlation functional with DFT-D3 (BJ) dispersion correction and TZP basis set incorporated with ZORA approach to include the scalar relativistic effects were employed under the spin-unrestricted scheme. A 5 × 5 slab with three atomic layers was used to mimic the Pd (100) surface with Cu doping. During the geometry optimizations, only the top layer was relaxed and the two bottom layers were frozen at the bulk positions. A 3 × 3 × 1 k-point grid was used to sample the first Brillouin zone under the two-dimensional PBC. A Γ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
